    "excerpt": "Writing is thinking made visible. It forces you to articulate ideas clearly.",
    "content": "Writing is thinking made visible. When you sit down to write, you're forced to articulate ideas clearly and coherently. The blank page is a mirror that reflects the gaps in your thinking.\n\nI've found that writing regularly has made me a clearer thinker. The discipline of putting words on a page, of arranging them in a way that makes sense, is the same discipline required to think deeply about a subject.\n\nStart writing about what you care about. Your unique perspective is valuable.",
